create a folder named input_data in the current directory and paste your files in 'fasta' format into it

To count indels, click on the cell below which contains the following code:

%run -m crispr_cas9.count_indels
after that to run the script do one of the following:

click Run button on the panel above
or press Shift + Enter or Ctrl + Enter
when the script finishes its work, the results will be written into the folder output_indels in the current directory

To create matrices, click on the cell below which contains the following code:
%run -m crispr_cas9.create_matrices
after that to run the script do one of the following:

click Run button on the panel above
or press Shift + Enter or Ctrl + Enter
when the script finishes its work, the results will be written into the folder output_matrices in the current directory

To create plots using the excel spreadsheets made by the previous command, click on the next cell with the code:
%run -m crispr_cas9.create_plots
and again to run the script do one of the following:

click Run button on the panel above
or press Shift + Enter or Ctrl + Enter
when this script finishes its work, the results will be written into the folder output_plots in the current directory

NOTES:

if you want to stop running script, click stop button on the panel above (which is black square).
import crispr_cas9
%run -m crispr_cas9.count_indels
